4. Can I work part-time while studying at Humanitas University Italy?
International students studying at Humanitas University Italy may be eligible to work part-time during their studies, subject to certain restrictions and regulations. The Italian government allows international students to work up to 20 hours per week during the academic year and full-time during scheduled breaks and holidays. However, it is important to check the specific work regulations and visa requirements for international students in Italy and consult with Qadri International Educational Consultants for guidance on employment opportunities.
